dataIdInfo.idPurp: JNCC collates boundary and attribute data on Special Conservation Areas (SACs) on behalf of the UK Statutory Nature Conservation Bodies, and formally submits these to the European Commission. A subset of the UK's SACs protect marine interest features or "marine components". This layer contains only the SACs that protect marine components, including inshore and offshore sites. This layer also contains any proposed SAC boundaries which are at the consultation/post-consultation phase. This file was last updated June 2020.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
JNCC collates boundary and attribute data on Special Conservation Areas (SACs) on behalf of the UK Statutory Nature Conservation Bodies, and formally submits these to the European Commission. A subset of the UK's SACs protect marine interest features or "marine components". This layer contains only the SACs that protect marine components, including inshore and offshore sites. This layer also contains any proposed SAC boundaries which are at the consultation/post-consultation phase. This file was last updated June 2020.

'SACs with marine components' were defined by the inter-agency Marine Natura Project Group in 2007, explained in:

http://data.jncc.gov.uk/data/0c1ec9ba-97c3-46e8-a274-6dac4ec92edf/MarineSAC-SelectionCriteria-030609.pdf

http://data.jncc.gov.uk/data/2724254e-3d7d-46e5-be9d-612fc4ab1f70/MN2KPG16-13-MN2KDefs.pdf

Attribute information:

This layer is projected in WGS 1984 geographic coordinate system, coordinates of the centroid for each site and it's area in Hectares are given in the attribute table.

Site dates

The Conslt Date is the date that the consultation on the boundary was launched. The cSAC Date is the date that candidate SACs were submitted to the European Commission and therefore the Habitat Regulations formally came into effect. The SCI Date is the date that the European Commission approves the site as a Site of Community Importance. The SAC Date is the date that the UK Government designated the site as a Special Area of Conservation. Where an extension to a site has been proposed and accepted the relevant site date has been updated, i.e. if the update is to a cSAC the cSACDate is updated but if a fully designated SAC boundary is extended, then the SACdate is updated.

Status

Site status is listed as designated once the site becomes a fully designated SAC, sites that are either cSAC or SCIs are listed as candidate under status.

Agency codes

The following agency codes are used in the attribute table: JNCC - Joint Nature Conservation Committee, SNH - Scottish Natural Heritage, NE - Natural England, NRW - Natural Resources Wales and DAERA - Department of Agriculture, Environment and Rural Affairs, Northern Ireland.

CP2 regions

The UK assessment of progress made towards the vision of ‘clean, healthy, safe, productive and biologically diverse oceans and seas’ known as Charting Progress 2 divided the entire UK sea area into eight biogeographic regions based on bio-geographical features such as physical parameters and the distribution of flora and fauna. More information is available at:

http://chartingprogress.defra.gov.uk/regional-basis-charting-progress-2. As such the CP2 reporting regions have been provided in this shapefile under 'CP2Region', a site may occur in more than one region.

Country

The Country attribute refers to the country/country waters that the MPA falls within. A single site may occur in more than one than one country.

WDPA Code

The identification number given to protected areas in the World Database on Protected Areas (www.protectedplanet.net). This is a globally unique identifier.

This version (02/06/2020) includes the following updates:

-Added Braunton Burrows SAC into dataset as this site is now considered to have a marine component.

  • Details of changes made in previous versions:

05/09/2019-Update of the status of Croker Carbonate Slabs from cSAC/SCI to fully designated SAC.

  • 25/02/2019- Change of status for 7sites from cSAC/SCIs to fully designated SACs: Bristol Channel Approaches / Dynesfeydd Môr Hafren, East Mingulay, Inner Hebrides and the Minches, North Anglesey Marine / Gogledd Môn Forol, North Channel, Southern North Sea and West Wales Marine / Gorllewin Cymru Forol.

  • 12/12/2018- Correction of the Flamborough Head SAC boundary to the latest version.

26/11/2018 - Update to Flamborough Head SAC following the post consultation acceptance of the boundary amendment.

12/09/2018 - Addition of 10 sites: Ardvar and Loch a' Mhuilinn Woodlands SAC, Durness SAC, Glen Beasdale SAC, Hascosay SAC, Inverpolly SAC, Kinloch and Kyleakin Hills SAC, Mull Oakwoods SAC, Rum SAC, Taynish and Knapdale Woods SAC, Tayvallich Juniper and Coast SAC. Updated site boundaries and attribute information for Braemar Pockmarks SAC and Scanner Pockmark SAC. Updated attribute information only for The Maidens SAC and Skerries and Causeway SAC.
